nodes.title: System Prompt
widgets_values:
You are a prompt conversion specialist. 
You will be given a tag-based prompt that uses comma separation and numerical weights (e.g., (word:1.2)). Your sole task is to analyze these tags and their weights to identify the core subject, action, environment, and style, then synthesize them into a single, descriptive prompt. This prompot will consist of at maximum ten sentences. Each sentence must be under 60 words. Desribe the expected iamge with natural, direct language that will produce a result following the expectations of the original prompt. 


A structured approach helps with the result:
1. Subject: Clearly define the central person, object, or theme.
2. Description and action: Use vivid adjectives and action verbs to elaborate on the subject and its activity. This adds depth and complexity.
3. Environment and setting: Describe the background and setting to provide context for the scene.
4. Style and medium: Indicate the desired artistic style, medium, or movement, such as "photo," "oil painting," "3D rendering," "impressionist," "cyberpunk," or by referencing an artist like "in the style of Van Gogh".
5. Lighting and atmosphere: Define the mood and lighting, using terms like "somber," "vibrant," "introspective," or descriptions such as "warm sunlight filtering through the trees". 
6. Technical details (optional): Include technical details like camera settings for more control, especially for photorealistic results, such as "Highly detailed, with realistic textures and global illumination". 

A suggested formula for prompts is: 
[Subject and Description], 
[Action and Interaction], 
[Environment and Setting], 
[Mood and Atmosphere], 
[Style and Technical Details]. 

Imperative: Your entire response must be only the final, converted prompt. Do not include any conversational text, labels, or explanations.

nodes.title: Concatenated result: Pre + Ollama
widgets_values:
.   A colossal, swirling galaxy glows with iridescent blues and purples, its spiral arms twisting like living vines against the midnight blackness.  
The galaxy radiates faint, shimmering light that refracts across the cosmic backdrop, creating a subtle aurora of distant stars.  
A lone, translucent spacecraft hovers near the galaxyâ€™s core, its hull pulsing with bioluminescent panels that echo the nebulaâ€™s colors.  
The scene is rendered as a hyperrealistic digital painting, with intricate pixel-level detail capturing the depth of space.  
Soft, dreamlike glows from the galaxyâ€™s gas clouds illuminate the surrounding darkness, casting gentle halos on the spacecraft.  
Vibrant, surreal color gradients merge at the edges, giving the galaxy a surreal, almost liquid quality.  
High dynamic range lighting and global illumination enhance the luminosity, making every star and filament appear vividly alive.

Keep group 01 (Positive Prompt) and 03 (Image Generation) to get an image.

Disable 02 (Ollama) to not use it.
The 02 group will only affect content coming from the "ImpactWildcardProcessor" text (from 01) to transform wildcards or enhance text provided into a narrative following the provided "system prompt".
It will not use content from the "Prelimary Text" section from the 01 group.
Connectiivity and Model availability are dependent on your installation.

In 03 (Image Generation), after loading a checkpoint, switch the "Mode" to match the model type: 1=Flux1D / 2=Qwen.
You can also set the resolution (Base Resolution) and other txt2img parameters in this group.
The "Batch Size" (in "Resolution") is useful for the "Image Selection" (04) group.

Skipping 04 (Image Selection) will not prevent the S1 (Stage 1) images from beging saved. When bypassed, all generated images will be saved, otherwise only selected ones.

- Useful to intercept image generations before they go to the next step.

- Meant to be used in an interactive mode.

- Control the amount of image generated by changing the "batch size" in the "Resolution" block

- Only selected images will be saved
